            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I am not saying that we will include this behavior, but _if_ we were to, this change should probably happen in `loader.get_source`: https://github.com/pallets/flask/blob/master/flask/templating.py#L54.\n\nHowever, I'm inclined to leave this as it is.  Allowing the app to override templates is a good behavior in my opinion.  Blueprint relative template references breaks this.  The only thing this gets you is typing `./` instead of `name/`.\n"
